                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18231203-106-off568 t18231203-106-crimeloc571"></join>. On the 11th of November, about twenty minutes past eight o'clock in the morning, this cotton stood on a stool inside the door; a boy informed me a man had stolen it; I missed it, went out, and found the prisoner, about a hundred yards off, with a bundle under his arm. I secured him in Drury-lane with it.</p>
